From: Giovanni Campagna <gcampagn@redhat.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Sep 2013 13:57:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Support GNOME Build API

By adding an autogen.sh file with NOCONFIGURE support.
---
 autogen.sh | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)
 create mode 100755 autogen.sh

diff --git a/autogen.sh b/autogen.sh
new file mode 100755
index 0000000..cf2c610
--- /dev/null
+++ b/autogen.sh
@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@
+#!/bin/sh
+
+test -n "$srcdir" || srcdir=`dirname "$0"`
+test -n "$srcdir" || srcdir=.
+
+olddir=`pwd`
+
+cd "$srcdir"
+test -d m4 || mkdir m4
+autoreconf -fvi || exit $?
+
+cd "$olddir"
+test -n "$NOCONFIGURE" || ./configure "$@"
